        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35941",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=drm",
                        "name": "drm",
                        "displayName": "Gerard van Helden",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Has to do with http:\/\/bugs.php.net\/bug.php?id=46335\r\n\r\nI have written a workaround for it, but it depends on mb_substr(). I'm not sure if it's ok for lucene to depend on multibyte. If not a problem, I'll submit the patch. \r\n\r\nBtw, I have only tested this on a debian lenny with php 5.2.6, so I'm not entirely sure the bug still exists in PHP at all. If not, this issue could be resolved anyway.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=drm",
                        "name": "drm",
                        "displayName": "Gerard van Helden",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-11T13:20:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-11T13:20:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36274",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stephane",
                        "name": "stephane",
                        "displayName": "St\u00e9phane",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just a quick comment to let you know that a pretty bad workaround is just to create an instance of the parser manually:\r\n\r\n{noformat} \r\n\/\/ Builds a list of words from the search terms\r\n$words = explode(' ', mb_strtolower($search));\r\n\r\n\/\/ Initializes the Lucene parser and tokenizes the excerpt\r\n$analyzer = new Zend_Search_Lucene_Analysis_Analyzer_Common_Utf8_CaseInsensitive();\r\n$analyzer->setInput($content, \"utf-8\");\r\n\r\n\/\/ Initializes a list of tokens for the search terms\r\n$tokens = array();\r\n\r\n\/\/ Retrieves the first token from the excerpt\r\n$token = $analyzer->nextToken();\r\n\r\n\/\/ Parses each token and processes only the ones corresponding to the\r\n\/\/ search terms\r\nwhile ($token !== null) {\r\n  \/\/ Stores any token found matching a search term\r\n  if (array_value_exists($token->getTermText(), $words)) {\r\n    $tokens[] = $token;\r\n  }\r\n  \r\n  $token = $analyzer->nextToken();\r\n}\r\n\r\n\/\/ Defines a padding to be able to compute the real position of each \r\n\/\/ token whenever some 'strong' tags is added to the excerpt\r\n$pad = 0;\r\n\r\nforeach ($tokens as $token) {\r\n  \/\/ Retrieves the position of the search term thanks to the token\r\n  $start = $token->getStartOffset() + $pad;\r\n  $end = $token->getEndOffset() + $pad;\r\n  \r\n  \/\/ Highlights the search term\r\n  $content = mb_substr($content, 0, $start) . \"<strong>\" . mb_substr($content, $start, $end - $start) . \"<\/strong>\" . mb_substr($content, $end);\r\n  \r\n  \/\/ Increases the padding\r\n  $pad += mb_strlen(\"<strong><\/strong>\"); \r\n}\r\n{noformat} ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stephane",
                        "name": "stephane",
                        "displayName": "St\u00e9phane",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-20T06:29:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-20T06:29:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36458",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=drm",
                        "name": "drm",
                        "displayName": "Gerard van Helden",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "My fix can be implemented with iconv too. Since that is an essential dependency of Zend_Search_Lucene anyway, I will submit a patch for it asap.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=drm",
                        "name": "drm",
                        "displayName": "Gerard van Helden",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-24T04:46:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-24T04:46:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42274",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nicolas.huguet",
                        "name": "nicolas.huguet",
                        "displayName": "Nicolas Huguet",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have the same problem.\r\nThe following changes to the file Zend\/Search\/Lucene\/Document\/Html.php seems to fix this problem in my case :\r\n\r\n{noformat} \r\n\r\n--- old 2010-09-17 17:02:04.000000000 +0200\r\n+++ new 2010-09-17 17:03:43.000000000 +0200\r\n@@ -306,11 +306,20 @@\r\n         $matchedTokens = array_reverse($matchedTokens);\r\n\r\n         foreach ($matchedTokens as $token) {\r\n+\r\n+            \/\/ Convert characters offset to bytes offsets\r\n+            \/\/ Because splitText() bellow does not handle multibytes characters\r\n+            \/\/ see http:\/\/bugs.php.net\/bug.php?id=46335\r\n+            $startOffset = $token->getStartOffset();\r\n+            $endOffset = $token->getEndOffset();\r\n+            $bytesStartOffset = strlen(mb_substr($node->wholeText, 0, $startOffset, 'UTF-8'));\r\n+            $bytesEndOffset = strlen(mb_substr($node->wholeText, 0, $endOffset, 'UTF-8'));\r\n+\r\n             \/\/ Cut text after matched token\r\n-            $node->splitText($token->getEndOffset());\r\n+            $node->splitText($bytesEndOffset);\r\n\r\n             \/\/ Cut matched node\r\n-            $matchedWordNode = $node->splitText($token->getStartOffset());\r\n+            $matchedWordNode = $node->splitText($bytesStartOffset);\r\n\r\n             \/\/ Retrieve HTML string representation for highlihted word\r\n             $fullCallbackparamsList = $params;\r\n\r\n\r\n{noformat} ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nicolas.huguet",
                        "name": "nicolas.huguet",
                        "displayName": "Nicolas Huguet",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-09-17T08:08:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-09-17T08:08:57.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
